Lightly coat a 12-inch skillet with cooking spray; heat over medium heat. In hot skillet cook pork, half at a time, until brown. Place meat in a 3 1/2- or 4-quart slow cooker. Add the onions and mushrooms. In a bowl stir together the soup and sage. Stir soup mixture into pork mixture in the cooker. Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 6 to 7 hours or on high-heat setting for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.